<subSubSection id="C35C6510FFCCED075231D3C9A49853F6" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9369BFFCCED075231D3C9A49853F6" blockId="22.[264,1325,799,1785]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCCED075231D3C9A69553A7" box="[312,414,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFCCED0752A6D3C9A53153A7" box="[431,570,1679,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inequalis">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCCED0752A6D3C9A53153A7" box="[431,570,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. inequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFCCED0751CBD3C9A43753A7" box="[706,828,1679,1704]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hussa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCCED0751CBD3C9A43753A7" box="[706,828,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
externally, but differs in the facial markings. Its male genitalia are similar to those of 
<emphasis id="B932EA89FFCCED07503FD3F1A4A753DF" box="[822,940,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="4C464D18FFCCED07503FD3F1A4A353DF" box="[822,936,1719,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knappi">S. knappi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from which it differs in having slender paraphyses and a tubular curved aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
